        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(perplexity): add search context size",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #84872.\n\nThe managed Perplexity `web_search` provider did not expose Perplexity's `low` / `medium` / `high` `search_context_size` content-budget knob, so agents could not ask for a smaller or richer extraction context through OpenClaw.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdds `search_context_size` to the shared model-facing `web_search` schema and the Perplexity provider schema, validates `low` / `medium` / `high`, forwards it to native Perplexity Search API requests, and carries it through Sonar/OpenRouter compatibility as `web_search_options.search_context_size`. The value is included in the cache key, and native Search API calls reject mixing `search_context_size` with `max_tokens` or `max_tokens_per_page`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo config changes. Existing calls keep the same behavior. Perplexity `web_search` callers can now choose `low`, `medium`, or `high` search context size, and invalid or conflicting content-budget inputs return actionable errors.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `corepack pnpm docs:list`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tools/web-search.test.ts extensions/perplexity/src/perplexity-web-search-provider.test.ts src/web-search/runtime.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `corepack pnpm format:check -- src/agents/tools/web-search.ts src/agents/tools/web-search.test.ts extensions/perplexity/src/perplexity-web-search-provider.ts extensions/perplexity/src/perplexity-web-search-provider.runtime.ts extensions/perplexity/src/perplexity-web-search-provider.test.ts docs/tools/perplexity-search.md docs/tools/web.md`\n- `OPENCLAW_EXTENSION_BOUNDARY_CONCURRENCY=6 corepack pnpm run lint:extensions:bundled`\n- `OPENCLAW_ADDITIONAL_BOUNDARY_SHARD=1/4 OPENCLAW_ADDITIONAL_BOUNDARY_CONCURRENCY=4 node scripts/run-additional-boundary-checks.mjs`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `corepack pnpm build`\n- GitHub commit verification for `4a823abb`: `verified=true`, `reason=valid`\n\nNo live Perplexity API request was run because this environment does not have a real Perplexity API key; request-body forwarding is covered with mocked guarded-fetch tests, and the source-level gap is reproducible without a live provider call.",
